tratification. This tightly integrated collection of essays, conceived and developed by the author in pursuit of corrective intervention in Plato’s metaphysics, combines his previously published work with newly drafted material for the present volume. The book replaces the standard view of Plato as a metaphysical dualist with a novel interpretation providing greater explanatory power through the paradigm of unitary pluralism in a single reality built on ontological diversity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aPhilosophy : Ancient Greek Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Epistemology. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : Metaphysics. 4aPsychology : Moral Psychology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh1 aSmith, Nicholas D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848565240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438485652423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438485652/original  a978-3-11-149169-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles